{"id":5,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":5,"title":"Chapter 3: Lehi Leaves Jerusalem","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 3"],["h1","Lehi Leaves Jerusalem"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p3"},"The Lord was pleased with Lehi and one night spoke to him in a dream. He told Lehi to take his family and leave Jerusalem. Lehi obeyed the Lord."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.1-3"},"1 Nephi 2:1–3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p5"},"Lehi’s family packed food and tents. They left their house and their gold and silver and traveled into the wilderness."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.4"},"1 Nephi 2:4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p7"},"Lehi and his wife, Sariah, had four sons. Their names were Laman, Lemuel, Sam, and Nephi."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.5"},"1 Nephi 2:5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p9"},"After traveling for three days, Lehi’s family camped in a valley near a river."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.6"},"1 Nephi 2:6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p11"},"Lehi built an altar from stones and made an offering to God. He thanked God for saving his family from being destroyed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.7"},"1 Nephi 2:7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p13"},"Lehi named the river Laman and the valley Lemuel. Lehi wanted his sons to be like the river and valley, continually flowing to God and steadfastly keeping the commandments."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.8-10,14"},"1 Nephi 2:8–10, 14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p15"},"Laman and Lemuel thought their father was foolish for leaving Jerusalem and their riches. They did not believe that Jerusalem would be destroyed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.11,13"},"1 Nephi 2:11, 13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p17"},"Nephi wanted to understand the things Lehi had seen. He prayed to know if his father had done the right thing by leaving Jerusalem."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.16"},"1 Nephi 2:16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p19"},"Jesus Christ visited Nephi and told him that Lehi’s words were true. Nephi believed and did not rebel as Laman and Lemuel did."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.16"},"1 Nephi 2:16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p21"},"Nephi told his brothers what Jesus had told him. Sam believed Nephi, but Laman and Lemuel would not believe."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.17-18"},"1 Nephi 2:17–18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_005_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p23"},"The Lord promised Nephi that he would be blessed because of his faith. He would become a leader over his brothers."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-3-lehi-leaves-jerusalem.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/2.19-22"},"1 Nephi 2:19–22"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
